article.headline: 18-7 first-half run puts Tigers in control
article.linkText: No. 16 LSU too much for Florida in SEC
article.story:
GAINESVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Seimone Augustus scored 26 points to
help No. 16 LSU beat No. 20 Florida 91-72 on Sunday, and maintain
their hold on second place in the Southeastern Conference.

The Tigers (20-4, 8-2 SEC) went on an 18-7 run near the end of
the first half to break a 22-22 tie and take control. LSU went on
an 11-2 spurt in the second half after the Gators (16-7, 6-4) cut
the deficit to 61-52 on Bernice Mosby's 3-pointer with 10:44 left.

The Tigers remained in second place in the SEC, one-half game
ahead of No. 14 Auburn, which beat South Carolina 69-58.

Thirteen of the LSU's first 14 baskets in the second half came
on layups, and they shot 61.3 percent for the game.

Temeka Johnson had 17 points and a game-high six assists for the
Tigers. Doneeka Hodges had all 15 of her points in the first half,
and Scholanda Hoston added 11 .

Augustus has had her two highest scoring games of the season
against Florida, scoring 28 points in at Baton Rouge on Jan. 15.

Mosby led the Gators with 19 points. Vanessa Hayden added 17
despite shooting just 7-for-24 with four turnovers.
